Arrays in kotlin

Val num = arrayOf(1,2,3,4,5)

Num.set(0,1)   index-->0  value-->1

Val numString = arrayOf<String>("1","2","3")    //MOST USED IN KOTLIN

Val numString = arrayOf<String>("1","2",3)   //This will not work bcoz we have initilized string type array

Val num = intArrayOf(1,2,3,4,5,6)    //only array of int type

Val num = arrayOf(size:6,{ i -> i*1} )    Output ----> 0,1,2,3,4,5

Val nullArray = arrayOfNull<String>(size:6) 
                            OR 
val nullArray  = arrayOfNullS<Student>()  Student is a class and we want to make array of children

IF USE DON’T WANT TO FILL THE ARRAY i.e You don’t know the values but size of array
Use
Val num = IntArray(4)   //say size=4
And set values as
Num.set(0,1)
Num.set(1,2);
